Description of the job

   A versatile experienced Systems Engineer is required to join a studies group, based in Portsmouth, working on advanced programmes for satellites navigation ground systems.

   The successful candidate will report to the Head of Product Studies and will take on significant responsibilities within the design team. In addition, they must have customer facing abilities, as the position entails technical exchanges and meetings with the customer Agencies (e.g.UK SA, UK MOD and ESA), other System Primes, Suppliers and Subcontractors.

   The role is highly technical and applicants must be proficient in a number of system engineering disciplines including RF systems, signal processing, software architecture and security. The working environment is within large scale complex Satellite Ground Systems for navigation and Satellite Navigation Reference Receivers.

Tasks &amp; accountabilities

   Your main tasks and responsibilities will include:
   - Requirements analysis and functional decomposition.
   - Delivery of incremental systems design and baseline design for some component solutions.
   - Technical analysis of system design issues
   - Performance budgeting
   - Interface definition
   - Authoring of technical specifications

   This role could involve some travel for business and as such you must be able to travel accordingly.

   This job requires an awareness of any potential compliance risks and a commitment to act with integrity, as the foundation for the Company's success, reputation and sustainable growth.

Required skills

   Essential Competencies/Qualities:
   - Degree Educated with proven relevant experience in
   - Systems engineering and / or systems architecting
   - RF System Design and Analysis
   - Signal Processing Analysis and Design
   - Software architecture (significant previous experience as a lead designer on a software system)
   - Requirements engineering
   - Review of element and system testing as part of acceptance.
   - Matlab
   - Python and C
   - Linux
   - Formal approach to documentation
   - Subcontract technical management

   Desirable Competencies:
   - Experience of GNSS
   - STK

